50|$|In {{international}} taxation, {{a physical}} presence test is a rule {{used to determine}} tax residence of a natural or legal person. It may rely on having a place of business in the jurisdiction (<b>for</b> <b>legal</b> <b>persons),</b> or remaining {{in or out of}} the jurisdiction for a certain number of days each year (for natural persons).|$|E
