50|$|In another provision, the law {{specifies}} obligations <b>for</b> public <b>legal</b> <b>persons</b> (government administrations, et al.), mandating {{the use of}} French in publications, or {{at least}} in summaries of publications. In France, it is a constitutional requirement that the public should be informed of the action of the government. Since the official language of France is French, it follows that the French public {{should be able to get}} official information in French.|$|R
